Items.description: Jim Thome hit a two-run homer after a nearly three-hour rain delay and the defending World Series champion White Sox beat the Indians 10-4 to open the 2006 major league season.
Items.title: White Sox home opener
Items.vs: Chicago White Sox vs. Cleveland Indians

Items.description: Tom Glavine outpitched Livan Hernandez in a matchup of World Series MVPs, newcomer Xavier Nady went 4-for-4 and David Wright homered to help the Mets edge the Nats 3-2.
Items.title: Mets home opener
Items.vs: New York Mets vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: Jeff Cirillo hit a go-ahead two-run single in the seventh inning that sparked Milwaukee to a 5-2 victory.
Items.title: Brewers home opener
Items.vs: Milwaukee Brewers vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: Curt Schilling looked a lot like his old self in his first Opening Day start in seven years. The debut of new Texas ace Kevin Millwood was a bust.
Items.title: Rangers home opener
Items.vs: Texas Rangers vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Chicago rolled to its fourth straight Opening Day victory, 16-7 over a Reds team that could bring the president to town but couldn't stop the Cubs' run of first-game success.
Items.title: Reds home opener
Items.vs: Cincinnati Reds vs. Chicago Cubs

Items.description: Luis Matos and Melvin Mora hit successive homers in the fifth inning and Miguel Tejada and Jeff Conine also connected, leading the O's past the Devil Rays 9-6.
Items.title: Orioles home opener
Items.vs: Baltimore Orioles vs. Tampa Bay Devil Rays

Items.description: Jimmy Rollins kept up his pursuit of Joe DiMaggio's major league-record 56-game hitting streak with a double in the eighth inning, but it was the lone bright spot for the Phillies in a 13-5 loss to the Cardinals.
Items.title: Phillies home opener
Items.vs: Philadelphia Phillies vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: Matt Holliday dashed home on a grounder and dived in ahead of the throw for the winning run in the 11th inning to give the Rockies a 3-2 win over the Diamondbacks.
Items.title: Rockies home opener
Items.vs: Colorado Rockies vs. Arizona Diamondbacks

Items.description: Kenny Rogers helped get Jim Leyland a win in his first game as the Detroit Tigers' manager.
Items.title: Royals home opener
Items.vs: Kansas City Royals vs. Detroit Tigers

Items.description: The Braves began their quest for a 15th straight division championship by building a quick seven-run lead, then hanging on as Tim Hudson and several relievers struggled.
Items.title: Dodgers home opener
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Atlanta Braves

Items.description: Orlando Cabrera's two-run single in the ninth inning lifted the Angels past the Mariners 5-4.
Items.title: Mariners home opener
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Los Angeles Angels

Items.description: Roy Oswalt and Brad Lidge combined on a five-hitter, Craig Biggio doubled and scored on Joe Borowski's wild pitch in the seventh inning and Houston beat Florida 1-0.
Items.title: Astros home opener
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. Florida Marlins

Items.description: Mike Piazza and Khalil Greene homered to lead the defending NL West champion Padres to a 6-1 win over Barry Bonds and the Giants.
Items.title: Padres home opener
Items.vs: San Diego Padres vs. San Francisco Giants

Items.description: Alex Rodriguez hit a grand slam and drove in five runs in the Yankees' 15-2 rout of the Athletics.
Items.title: Athletics home opener
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. New York Yankees

Items.description: Aaron Boone took some glimmer off Chicago's ring ceremony, lifting the Indians to an 8-2 victory over the White Sox.
Items.vs: Chicago White Sox vs. Cleveland Indians

Items.description: Roy Halladay outpitched Johan Santana in a matchup of recent Cy Young Award winners as the Blue Jays posted a 6-3 win over the Twins.
Items.title: Blue Jays home opener
Items.vs: Toronto Blue Jays vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: The rookie-laden Marlins roughed up Andy Pettitte for 10 runs and 13 hits Tuesday night in an 11-2 rout of the Astros.
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. Florida Marlins

Items.description: Capuano pitched six solid innings and Damian Miller drove in three runs as the Milwaukee Brewers posted a 7-5 victory over the Pittsburgh Pirates.
Items.vs: Milwaukee Brewers vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: Phil Nevin had a three-run homer in the first inning and later chased struggling Tim Wakefield with a two-run single, leading the Rangers to a 10-4 win over the Red Sox.
Items.vs: Texas Rangers vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Marco Scutaro singled over left fielder Hideki Matsui's head in the bottom of the ninth, giving the Athletics a 4-3 victory over the Yankees.
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. New York Yankees

Items.description: The weather in San Diego gave Barry Bonds a break from fan abuse.
Items.vs: San Diego Padres vs. San Francisco Giants

Items.description: Richie Sexson had three hits and five RBIs and Kenji Johjima homered in his second straight game to lead the Mariners to a 10-8 win over the Angels.
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Los Angeles Angels

Items.description: Brad Penny pitched five strong innings, J.D. Drew hit a two-run homer and Los Angeles beat Atlanta 5-4 for Grady Little's first victory as the Dodgers' manager.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Atlanta Braves

Items.description: Ken Griffey Jr.'s 537th career homer got upstaged by Bronson Arroyo's first.
Items.vs: Cincinnati Reds vs. Chicago Cubs

Items.description: Jason Michaels doubled in the go-ahead run in the 11th inning -- his fourth hit of the game -- and the Indians beat the White Sox 4-3 to take two of three in the opening series.
Items.vs: Chicago White Sox vs. Cleveland Indians

Items.description: Ivan Rodriguez was 5-for-5 with a single, homer, three doubles and five RBI, leading the Tigers to a 14-3 rout of the Royals.
Items.vs: Kansas City Royals vs. Detroit Tigers

Items.description: Jarrod Washburn bested Jeff Weaver in a matchup of pitchers making debuts for new teams.
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Los Angeles Angels

Items.description: Jay Gibbons homered and drove in four runs and Baltimore used a 16-hit attack to breeze past the Devil Rays 16-6.
Items.vs: Baltimore Orioles vs. Tampa Bay Devil Rays

Items.description: Yadier Molina's two-out RBI single off Tom Gordon in the ninth inning lifted the Cardinals to a 4-3 victory over the Phillies.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Phillies vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: Torii Hunter hit a grand slam and tied a career high with six RBI, leading the Twins to a 13-4 victory over the Blue Jays.
Items.vs: Toronto Blue Jays vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: Ryan Zimmerman hit a tying homer off new Mets closer Billy Wagner and Jose Guillen's two-run shot in the 10th lifted the Nats to a 9-5 win over the Mets.
Items.vs: New York Mets vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: Lance Berkman and Preston Wilson each hit two-run homers and the Astros held on for a 6-5 win over the Marlins.
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. Florida Marlins

Items.description: Prince Fielder hit a looping single that scored Geoff Jenkins in the eighth inning and lifted the Brewers to a 3-2 win over the Pirates.
Items.vs: Milwaukee Brewers vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: Josh Beckett pitched seven innings to win his Boston debut and Trot Nixon hit a two-run homer in the Red Sox's 2-1 victory over the Rangers.
Items.vs: Texas Rangers vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Orlando Hernandez struck out eight in five innings as the Diamondbacks beat the Rockies 4-2 om Wednesday.
Items.vs: Colorado Rockies vs. Arizona Diamondbacks

Items.description: Milton Bradley had three RBI and scored the go-ahead run on Robinson Cano's eighth-inning error, leading the Athletics to a 9-4 win over the visiting Yankees.
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. New York Yankees

Items.description: Barry Bonds reached base three times without getting a hit and scored once as the Giants beat the Padres 3-1 on Wednesday night.
Items.vs: San Diego Padres vs. San Francisco Giants

Items.description: Ryan Langerhans hit a two-out ground-rule double in the eighth to drive in the go-ahead run, and the Braves beat the Dodgers 9-8 Wednesday night.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Atlanta Braves

Items.description: Jimmy Rollins' hitting streak is over. The Philadelphia Phillies' losing streak keeps going.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Phillies vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: Barry Bonds drew his first two intentional walks of the season, struck out and grounded weakly to first Thursday in the San Francisco Giants' home opener, a 6-4 win over the Atlanta Braves.
Items.title: Giants home opener
Items.vs: San Francisco Giants vs. Atlanta Braves

Items.description: Facing a team that scored 25 runs in its first two games, Mark Hendrickson pitched a three-hitter to lead the Tampa Bay Devil Rays past the Baltimore Orioles 2-0 Thursday night.
Items.vs: Baltimore Orioles vs. Tampa Bay Devil Rays

Items.description: Gustavo Chacin made a strong first start, Jason Phillips hit a tiebreaking double and B.J. Ryan got his second save, leading the Blue Jays over the Minnesota Twins 6-3 Thursday night.
Items.vs: Toronto Blue Jays vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: Adam Dunn hit a 479-foot homer that bounced out of the ballpark, and followed with a disputed tiebreaking single in the eighth inning Thursday night, leading the Cincinnati Reds to a 6-5 victory over the winless Pittsburgh Pirates.
Items.vs: Cincinnati Reds vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: Carlos Beltran homered and drove in four runs, and Carlos Delgado also connected to help Pedro Martinez win his first start of the season as the New York Mets beat the Washington Nationals 10-5 Thursday night.
Items.vs: New York Mets vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: Knuckleballer R.A. Dickey allowed six home runs to Detroit on Thursday night, tying the post-1900 major league record in the Texas Rangers' 10-6 loss to the Tigers.
Items.vs: Texas Rangers vs. Detroit Tigers

Items.description: Miguel Batista matched a career high with 11 strikeouts in seven strong innings to win his first start in almost two seasons, leading the Arizona Diamondbacks to a 12-5 win over the Colorado Rockies on Thursday night.
Items.vs: Colorado Rockies vs. Arizona Diamondbacks

Items.description: Gil Meche put together another strong outing for a Seattle starter, and Carl Everett hit his first homer with the Mariners in a 6-2 win over the Oakland Athletics on Thursday night.
Items.vs: Seattle Mariners vs. Oakland Athletics

Items.description: Greg Maddux pitched neatly into the seventh inning, Derrek Lee hit his second homer of the season and the Chicago Cubs beat the Cardinals 5-1.
Items.title: Cubs home opener
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: Casey Blake hit a two-out grand slam, Travis Hafner homered twice and Paul Byrd pitched long enough to win a start he had waited 15 years for, helping the Indians roll to an 11-6 home-opening win over the Minnesota Twins on Friday.
Items.title: Indians home opener
Items.vs: Cleveland Indians vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: Daniel Cabrera walked six batters in the first inning, and the Boston Red Sox got 16 hits to back an efficient pitching performance by Matt Clement in a 14-8 victory over the Baltimore Orioles on Friday night.
Items.vs: Baltimore Orioles vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Brett Tomko pitched six effective innings and the Dodgers took advantage of sloppy defense to beat the Phillies 5-3 on Friday night.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Phillies vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Jonny Gomes hit a tiebreaking, two-run homer in the seventh inning and the Tampa Bay Devil Rays rallied from a six-run deficit to beat the Toronto Blue Jays 9-8 on Friday night.
Items.vs: Toronto Blue Jays vs. Tampa Bay Devil Rays

Items.description: Felipe Lopez homered twice and drove in three runs Friday night, leading the Reds to a 7-6 win over the Pirates.
Items.vs: Cincinnati Reds vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: Steve Trachsel pitched three-hit ball through six innings and drove in a run with the 10,000th double in team history as the Mets beat the Marlins 9-3 on Friday night.
Items.vs: New York Mets vs. Florida Marlins

Items.description: Lance Berkman and Preston Wilson hit two-run homers in the same inning for the second consecutive game to lead the Astros to a 6-1 win over the Nationals.
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: Dave Bush gave up two hits in seven innings and Derrick Turnbow got his fourth save in four games to help the Brewers beat the Diamondbacks 3-1.
Items.vs: Milwaukee Brewers vs. Arizona Diamondbacks

Items.description: Chris Shelton pushed his major league-leading home run total to five with a two-run drive and the Detroit Tigers remained the AL's only unbeaten team with a 5-2 victory over the Texas Rangers on Friday night.
Items.vs: Texas Rangers vs. Detroit Tigers

Items.description: Doug Mientkiewicz, Angel Berroa and John Buck had two RBIs apiece and Kansas City made up a six-run deficit in an 11-7 win over the Chicago White Sox on Friday night.
Items.vs: Kansas City Royals vs. Chicago White Sox

Items.description: Orlando Cabrera hit a two-run homer, Kelvim Escobar stifled most of New York's big hitters and the Los Angeles Angels beat the Yankees 4-1 Friday night in their home opener.
Items.title: Angels home opener
Items.vs: Los Angeles Angels vs. New York Yankees
